race.comment: MY TESTIMONY (7) gets the blinkers on for the first time today after being tested in stronger company last time out. The claim of Tsang means she'll carry no weight and she has enough early speed to cross from out wide. Can be tough to run down from up front. NISTIRITH (6) returned in good order when jumping the race favourite, being gunned down late. The form out of that race has been super and she'll be fitter for that effort. She's another with good early speed and can be tough to run down. TANGLE FOOT (11) is on debut for the Simon Miller yard with Pike in the saddle. Pike hasn't ridden her at the trials, but his booking is a good push for her chances. Can make an impression. ACTION NOT TALK (2) hasn't been far away in her trials where she's shown some versatility. Can be thereabouts on debut. ADMIRE BELLE (10) is another who has trialled nicely this time in work and she can't be discounted.
